content: Just the perfect game.
Its really fun but it's annoying how when you run out of inventory space I cannot find an obvious way to see/delete items I don't want to make room for new ones

Amazing. I had started on the first Dungeon warfare through Google play pass and I loved it. As soon as I discovered there was a DW2 I did not hesitate to spend money getting it. Yes the game is super difficult when you first start out but keep at it and soon you will feel like a true Dungeon warlord and the game will be over before you know it. After defeating the last Dungeon it was going to let me go on to something but the game was on my tablet that got ran over.

Can you add daily rewards and in-app purchases please? Can you make enemy stats the same as their encyclopedia stats in game please? When will you respond? Can you at least add a mode where you send heroes to attack dungeons please?
Superb tower defense, the best after kingdom rush with huge replayability, no iap
Custom level editor please
I didn't think they could out do the first, but Dungeon Warfare 2 is not only better than the first, it's the best Tower Defense game ever made.
Fun and hard td that has a few unique things about it.doesnt feel too grindy tons of different options to do maps.
Make sure you manually save.
Genuis TD
The perfect tower defense game. Absolutely love it with 0 micro transactions. Perfectly balanced and really fun to play
Best td on phone. Very high replayability
Great game, fun to test your creativity im picking the combination of towers. Also has a convenient full respec method, so you can always just reallocate your skills to whichever you feel like.

Almost a perfect game. Would give 5 stars if it weren't for one thing. You have to be level 30 to play endless. Due to the difficulty ramp early on, I think it should be lowered, to give players something else to go to sooner, to help level up and learn the game in a more free environment. Other than that it's probably my second favorite tower defense. Right up there with bloons. If the endless level gets changed it might even be above bloons.

Love it! Played the first one for many hours and glad to see level II is out. Good graphics and challenging play. Some levels are tough and you have to grind through to get the necessary resources, but it's fun. Made it through the first and second (Ascension) waves and it was a blast. Can't wait for Dungeon Warfare 3...
Full of potential, but too many bugs that apparently won't be fixed (last update was in 2019). Quite sad, since the game is a lot of fun otherwise.
Great Game to play for Hours
Fantasic game. A really fun and challenging experience. I was unsure about paying upfront but its worth it as then you have a full fun experience. Reminds me of the good old days of gaming.

A TD game with interesting mechanics! For sure in my top three with Bloons TD. The tower chaining combinations are unconstraining. Leveling, acsencion, and replayability (with free rune mods) has been great. Never had a bug and the controls are crisp. There are more map drops once you ascend. I've scratched my head a few times on which approaches would be best after flops. Grabbed this one after playing the first. This one has notable improvement in features and depth. Great job on the game.
Fixed the issue overnight! 5 üåü

Best tower defense game option on the Play Store. 5‚òÜ ... well worth the money. The game is flexible enough to experiment with different strategies. Battles are pretty short so you can progress on the go. Great overall game play and design.
So far in really enjoying the game. What would be cool, is if you made a map creator that people who bought the game can share with each other. Just a thought. Great game.
Fun but i cant get one of the side missions of surviving a wave with wrath level 6. Went all the way up to around level 13 and it still wouldnt complete the mission. What am I doing wrong?
Best tower defense game out there. Lots of levels to play and different strategies to try out and ensures mode as well as randomly generated levels to keep you coming back.

Amazing. Just as good as the first, well worth the (one-time) price. Small bug: sometimes when trying to increase a trap mastery it will gray out the + when you have enough points. Decreasing another skill will let you increase it, then you can re-increase the other skill.
Give me Dungeon Warfare 3. This is one of the best, if not the best, pure tower defense game on Android. After playing this you will realize all other tower defenses are made for kids.
The absolute best tower defense game outside of Warcraft 3. Highly recommend
Impressive game!
Best td I played in a long time besides Bloons
Controls are responsive, and everything is readable on a mobile. Its good. Switch version is good too. Recommended
This is a must have for me. I've played it so many times. Well worth the money and eagerly awaiting the next in the series.
Perfect tower defense. I will fight anybody who says otherwise.
Very hard, and exploits any mistakes you make.
Wow love it
Fun!!! Challenging, but there's always something achievable you can do at your level. It's the poster child for replayability. Can easily rearrange earned points to try new strategies.
achievements dont sync. pls fix for 5 stars. tnx
Really really really good.
Fantastic Tower Defense style game, definitely worth the original price but you should not miss the sale.
Good tower defense with no in-app purchases. More games should be like this.
Good fun, I think the game could be a bit quicker.
If you like tower defense this game is AMAZING
Great mazing tower d game
A heavily refined and upgraded version of the first installment - even more fun!
Would give 6 stars if I could. Great pay once game.
epic, grungy, and awesome TD can always make this game a challenge, reminds me good old days of dungeon keeper
Very good. Only lacks events, could have more kinds of guards and enemies , girls mages, etc
Fantastic game, with even more options than the first one
fantastic
Great game with incredible depth- dozens and dozens of maps and hours of interesting gameplay. My favourite TD game ever.
Love this game. If more mobile games were like this I think mobile might be able to give consoles a run for their money.
Even better than the first. Hands down my favorite mobile game
A worthy successor.
Great time killer, kids like playing too.
great!

It's Dungeon Keeper meets Gemcraft in this tower defense game. Unlike most tower defense games, you have to take moving terrains into account, along with special units behaviors that can mess your pathing. You also have customizable difficulty for your grinding needs, along with challenge objectives, giving replay value as you experiment with what you can come up with.
A real game for android. Very fun with a large variety of meaninhful traps to choose from.

This is a very challenging game that may seem impossible at times, but stick through it and it provides a satisfying experience when you beat levels. I will say the concept of changing paths for enemies make it slightly awkward where you decide to place towers, so i find myself always placing them in places where enemies will definitely cross (entrance/end) as well as forcing them on a specific path if possible through barricades. other than that, it's a fun game, but very difficult
one of the best TD games on the market, lots of levels, lots of towers, upgrades, runes, challenging, allows creativity in tower placement and types. highly reccomend for any TD lover.
no p2w no bs plus one of the best games for android. Orcs must die! in 2d. really lin3ke it
This really reminds me of Gemcraft Labyrinth and thats a good thing. This game is worth every single penny.
What mobile gaming should be! No microtransactions. Smooth running. Endless replayability. Tons of content. Unique in its genre. Builds perfectly from its last iteration.

Game is well designed. I like the variety of levels and the variety of traps is great. The amount of tiers for traps needs to be increased though and I hate that I can only get a single tier 3 upgrade per game.

This tower defence game is addictive as hell!! Better yet, no ads, no DLC, no data connection required! Awesome work devs! I should note I bought the first game and played it to death, but I never thought the second would be so much better!!
Incredible game, just like the first
did not care for the way the UI is and the way interacting with icons. it's a mess.

I really like this game. It is an excellent Tower Defense. I just have one problem. When you play a new map, the developer should indicate all the places where the enemies can emerge. It seems unfair to say "oh yeah enemies can suddenly appear from this entrance" after you have already built a system. After I play the map one time I am aware of the places from where the enemies enter the screen but it is pretty much an auto loss the first time you play a map. That is not good AI.
Must have game if you like tower defense games. No IAP or ads. The unlockables are nice, even better you can undo your upgrades for every level. Go buy, you will get more bang for you buck&time.
Great!! Not as simple and fun as the first. But still amazing. I could play this forever.

If you've played the original Dungeon Warfare, you know what your getting into, its that but better. For new people, this game can challenge Bloons and other TD games easily, mazing, tons of towers with plenty of variety in upgrading, skill trees, items to give passive buffs, runes to increase point multipliers while increasing difficulty, plenty of basic maps to fill your time and tons of randomised maps. Well worth the money.

Tons of replay value. Tons of traps. Tons of strategy options. Amazing game! So many options added for this 2nd game... Once a third game is made i will already be drooling just imaging what will be in it. Thanks for a great game. Price is right too.
probably needs a few balance adjustments and there are one or two minor bugs, but overall it's one of the better tower defense games I've ever played. well worth the couple bucks it costs.
simply the best tower defense game i have played. premium, high quality experience
Excellent game. If you enjoyed the Orcs Must Die series on PC then you will like this one.
Great defense game! Both this and the first part. You will find it really challenging.
Loved the original, and loving this one so far! A little harder than the first game based on my memory, but that's not a bad thing
like lol go hunter as the 20 zoom as 100
it's a cool game with a high difficulty spike when they introduce flying enemies.
clearly made with passion
great sequel to the original. just as entertaining woth new and somialr features. well worth the price

On the first glance this looks very similar to the first dungeon warfare, but dang it has so much more nuance. Love it!! <3 If there's a 3rd one, please port it over to android! :D Thanks for a wonderful TD game

Battery hog, but fun as hell! i LOVED the first one...played the HELL out of it! cant really play this one though. :( it drained my battery from 60% to 25% in 5 minutes! please optimize this game! PLEASE! I really wanna play it!
This brings me back to the golden days of flash games. Back when games had soul and the idle games didn't grip the attention of the brainless masses.
Not as good as the original, but still better than most other TD games to be played.

Incredible, for me the previous dungeon warfare ran out of replayability. This one has fixed that with random loot you can find (no in app purchases). The amount and rarity can be changed by rushing waves and getting perks. New exciting enemies have been added, increasing the strategy required to combat them. I do wish there were random unique bosses with ridiculous skills to add even more craziness to battle. It's also being frequently updated too. All in all a great buy.

A sequwl to one of the best tower defense games out there, the developer did well improving this game without tinkering too nuch with the original formula. Just like the first game, there are no in app purchases. You pay money once for a well made, well balanced game. If they fix the incredibly annoying 'rush all waves' objective, this would be perfect.

Better than the first one (which is really saying something), better graphics, trap design, level design, difficulty ramps, new mechanics, etc. *STILL* no micro transactions. DW2 is really worth your money and will provide a lot of time spent figuring out the right trap placements as you move through the levels. Additionally, they added support for the s-pen. I emailed about it, and I don't know if that's why they added it, but it just makes this type of game more fun for me. Buy it already!

As of today May 1, 2019 the new update added support for the S Pen. I am so happy for this update. I have a tendency for most apps or games if they dont function with the S Pen just closing them and never using them again. I enjoyed the game but needed my SPen. Thanks dev's for listening to feedback and adding support.
just wow!! so fun! i loved the first and played it on the comp
great game that builds on the strengths of the first Dungeon Warfare. very fun and challenging.
an amazing TD games. totally customizable and no iap. just awesome
a decent game, but it's cramped for large fingers, and doesn't work with Samsung s-pen. change that and I'll raise the score.
The devs put a lot of care and thought into making this game really interesting with great replayability.

Went ahead and bought the game since I enjoyed the first one quite a bit. Unfortunately, the game won't even start on my phome, simply sitting at a black screen. For developer information, I'm on a Moto G6 Play with Android version 8.0.0.
replyContent:
Hello, Vanfisa Pate.
On some devices, start up take long time than expect. Game will be started if you wait on black screen.
We're finding solution to solve the problem. Sorry for the inconvenience.

content: Excellent game. loads of content, cool fun, and absolutely zero ads or freemium stuff.
Again a great game! No horrible IAP üëç
One of the best tower defense games I've seen in the play store, and even better than the first. I gotta also say thank you so much for keeping it away from a pay to do anything garbage model.

The long awaited sequel to a great game. There are a couple of issues but I'm sure that in time those will be resolved. Recommendations/feature requests: - in-game explanation of map symbols. I'm doing it by trial and error right now - buttons to add/remove all points in a trap skill. To makes it easier to change specialties. - the ability to view trap skill trees outside of battle - some way to easily view map scores for regular and endless. So that we know which ones we have to go back to.
Awesome game, played the first one and the sequel does not disappoint.

Dungeon Warfare is one of my absolute favorite mobile games. The sequel is bigger, beefier, and far more complex. It is absolutely fantastic! If you like tower defense at all, this game is 100% for you.

DW1 is one of my top 3 tower defense games, and DW2 has improved on it in every way, while still keeping the great look and feel of the original. There's much better balance in this game, and many cool new enemies and traps. The only bit of confusion I have is whether rubies are the only way to acquire additonal traps, or whether any might be accessed through vaults.
I have already played it on PC, and finally now I can play it on the go. For any fan of tower defence genre and some gratouitious 8-bit violence this game is simply a must! Buy it right now! :)

good game but disappointing,only problem I have, is alot of the content from the last game was used here ,even the same music was?,for a premium price I expect all new content,we should not be seeing the same towers.a map creator would of made this game live for years,let us create custom maps and share with the world to play.those maps could be endless mode and have a high score,world leaderboards.
Great sequel with new graphics, more violence and cool deadly traps. One of the best TD.
Incredible Sequel
